Abdomen brown with first three segments lighter. Terminalia (
Fig. 2
) dark brown except lighter gonostyli. Tergite 9 trapezoid. Gonocoxite with row of blackish spinules along ventroapical margin. Gonostylus with two lobes: ventral lobe with apical spine; dorsal lobe didymous with subapical spine on the blunt ventral part while the dorsal part is tapering and slightly curved apically. Cercus with 10 combs of retinacula.
